1. Remove supernatant very carefully, avoiding debris.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"caqvf","text":"2. Using ice-cold DPBS+RNase Inhibitors, resuspend and combine the pellets from each tube into a total of 1 mL nuclei solution in a new tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fokr9","text":"3. Add Hoechst 33342 (dil: 1:1000): Dilute the Hoechst 1:10 (5 µL + 45 µL DPBS), then add 5 µL to 1 mL sample.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2c1pk","text":"4. Incubate on ice for 5 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fsqs7","text":"5. Mix 10 µL Nuclei suspension with 10 µL Trypan Blue and mix by pipetting.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6scjb","text":"6. Add 10 µL stained solution to a Cell Counter Slide and read using the Bio-Rad Cell Counter TC-20.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3edp7","text":"        Note: Nuclei count is Total Count minus Live Count

